Author: Vansh Singh Ruhela [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0009-0004-1750-3592>)
Maintainer: Vansh Singh Ruhela <hadesllm@proton.me>
Description: Backwards-compatibility shim for the package previously
  published as 'moirais'. The toolkit was renamed to 'morie' in version
  0.2.0. Loading 'moirais' attaches 'morie' and emits a one-time
  deprecation message; all functionality is provided by 'morie'.
  This shim is intended only to keep existing scripts working; new
  code should depend on 'morie' directly. The 'morie' package is
  listed under Suggests (not Depends) so that the shim installs
  even when 'morie' is not yet available in the same build batch
  (relevant for r-universe parallel builds); 'morie' is required
  at attach time and a clear error message is shown if absent.
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
  R (>= 4.3.0)
Suggests:
  morie (>= 0.2.0)
URL: https://github.com/hadesllm/morie
BugReports: https://github.com/hadesllm/morie/issues
